<div class="article-body" id="Body"><p class="no-indent">Anybody who knows me knows I’m the first to cut up and have fun, but as a daddy, I do have my serious moments. Jack is quick to point out these times to me and say, “Dad, I don’t want you to be serious right now.” Usually it’s right around homework, bedtime, or getting ready for school! </p><br/><p class="no-indent">But at supper, I encourage laughter and family conviviality. And there’s nothing like playing with raw pasta to bring out the giggles in the kids. The noodle fun leads the way to one of our favorite suppers—Spaghetti and Meatballs. The recipe includes mini turkey pepperoni in the sauce, which means the leftovers only get better sitting in the fridge. And that’s a good thing just in case Dad encounters a midnight snack attack. </p><br/><p class="no-indent">Until next time, y’all do good things.</p></div>
